get.description:
Use this endpoint to get details about a specific listing.

When requesting a specific listsing an expanded view of the listing is provided which includes comparables as well as the MLS history for the specific property. This is useful for building single property views within your app or website.

parameters.name: boardId
parameters.description: Filter by boardId. This is only required if your account has access to more than one MLS.

parameters.name: mlsNumber
parameters.description: (Required) The MLS number of the listing you wish to retrieve.

get.description:
Provide this endpoint with an mls number and it'll retrieve similar properties that are also for sale.

This is really useful if you'd like to show your users other properties they may be interested in.

By default this endpoint will retrieve similar properties in the same neighborhood, however you can override this by using a radius parameter.

parameters.name: boardId
parameters.description: Filter by boardId. This is only required if your account has access to more than one MLS. You may specify one or more board IDs to filter by, if not specified, returns all boards that that account has access to be default.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: Use if you want to limit the response to containing certain fields only. For example: fields?listPrice,soldPrice would limit the response to contain listPrice and soldPrice only. You can also specify the amount of images to return, for example if a listing has 40 images total and you specify fields=images[5] it will only return the first 5 images.

parameters.name: listPriceRange
parameters.description: If specified, returns similar listings whose listPrice are +/- the supplied value, for a given listing. For example, if the given listing is 1M and listPriceRange is 250k, similar listings between 750k and 1.25M will be returned.

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: If specified, will show similar listings within the specified radius (km). If not specified, defaults to showing listings in the same neighborhood.

parameters.description:

parameters.name: mlsNumber
parameters.description: (Required) The MLS number of the listing you wish to retrieve similar listings for.

For more information refer to The Searching, Filtering and Paginating Listings Guide .

Using this endpoint you can also request market statistics, dynamic map clusters and search images using AI.
